## v2.4.0 (2026-04-25)
**Changed by:** ProjectTelemachy myrmidon-swarm pass (2026-04-25)
**Verification:** verified-local

### What changed
- Added "Per-File Mega-Agent Pattern" subsection to Verified Workflow
- Added contention threshold rule (1-2 / 3-5 / 6+ issues per file)
- Added cross-file ordering rule for dependent mega-agents
- Added "File Contention Analysis Script" to Results & Parameters Quick Reference
- Added Failed Attempts entry for strict-per-wave on high-contention repos
- Added 2 new Wave Sizing rows for ProjectTelemachy (Wave D + Wave E mega-agents)
- Added ProjectTelemachy Verified On row
- Updated Overview outcome to include ProjectTelemachy results
- Bumped version from 2.3.0 to 2.4.0

### Why
ProjectTelemachy had executor.py (11 issues), models.py (8), cli.py (9), agamemnon_client.py (6).
The strict "1 issue per wave" approach would have required 12+ waves. Per-file mega-agents
collapsed this to Wave D (3 parallel Sonnet agents) + Wave E (1 solo executor agent).
17 PRs merged. Pattern is worth preserving explicitly.

