## v2.1.0 (2026-04-10)

**Changed by:** ProjectScylla batch triage session — 80-issue triage pass (20 already-done closures + ~18 PRs)
**Verification:** verified-local

### What changed

- Added "Pre-commit Environment Mismatch (System Python 3.9 / Go Version)" Critical Pitfall section
- Added "Audit Doc Policy Violations Hook Is Very Slow" Critical Pitfall section
- Added "Auto-merge Cleared on Force-Push" Critical Pitfall section
- Added 2 new Failed Attempts rows: "Audit Doc Policy Violations hook stall" and "Pre-commit hooks fail on system Python 3.9 / Go mismatch"
- Added 3 new Wave Sizing rows for ProjectScylla April 2026 session (Wave 0 close-only, Wave 1 Haiku, Wave 2a+2b Sonnet)
- Added new Verified On row for ProjectScylla 80-issue triage
- Added `verification` and `history` frontmatter fields
- Bumped version from 2.0.0 to 2.1.0

### Why

Previous v2.0.0 documented most wave execution patterns but lacked:
1. The pre-commit environment mismatch when system Python is 3.9 (Debian) — yamllint/gitleaks both fail locally
2. The "Audit Doc Policy Violations" hook slowness that freezes agents for 5+ minutes
3. The auto-merge cleared on force-push pattern (already partially covered in batch-pr-ci-fix-workflow but not here)
4. Session stats from the April 2026 batch triage that confirmed the wave pattern works for MEDIUM issues with Sonnet agents

